data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['leizə]
*danh từ
 ■(kỹ thuật) la-de

Anh - Anh
laser
■ noun a device that generates an intense narrow beam of coherent monochromatic light by stimulating the emission of photons from excited atoms or molecules.
Origin
1960s: acronym from light amplification by stimulated emission of radiation, based on the earlier maser.
